Conclusion
This project successfully demonstrated a complete VLSI design cycle for a non-trivial digital system:

Low-Level Design: Understanding and implementing gate-level logic (Decimal to BCD).

Module Design: Creating optimized, reusable modules for fundamental operations (Comparator, Adder, Subtractor).

System Integration: Combining these modules using a smart control strategy (9's complement) to build a more complex Arithmetic Unit.

Verification: Using industry-standard tools (Quartus, EDA Playground) to simulate, synthesize, and validate the design. This provides practical experience with a standard digital design workflow.
